<div><h3>ART 1140 - Exploring New Forms : Combining Ceramics and Textile Arts </h3>  <hr>Explores the historical, traditional and contemporary artistic applications of these two plastic mediums. Students will gain a working knowledge of traditional and experimental ceramic and fiber techniques. Design quality will be stressed throughout as a fundamental aspect of good craftsmanship. Students will gain an understanding of the artistic heritage inherent in crafts of the past and present. Material fee applies and is payable to Craft Studio on first night of class.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> varied<br><br></div>		</td>
